---
id: org.dxos.plugin.markdown
name: MarkdownPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Collaborative markdown editor plugin for `DXOS` Composer.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |

## Types

```mdl
type ViewMode
  literals: source | preview | readonly
```

```mdl
type Document
  fields:
    name?: string
    fallbackName?: string
    description?: string
    content: Ref<Text>          # collaborative text payload
```

```mdl
type Settings
  fields:
    defaultViewMode: ViewMode
    toolbar?: boolean
    numberedHeadings?: boolean
    folding?: boolean
    editorInputMode?: string    # default | vim | vscode
    commentAgentMode?: off | auto | mention
    experimental?: boolean
    debug?: boolean
```

## Components

```mdl
component MarkdownArticle
  desc: Full-surface markdown editor for a Document or Text subject.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text
    viewMode: ViewMode
    settings: Settings
  state:
    selection?: range           # current editor selection
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode         # formatting toolbar (when settings.toolbar)
  actions:
    setViewMode(mode: ViewMode)
    uploadFile(file: File) → Ref<Image>
  emits:
    onSelectObject(id: string)  # follow @ref or link
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar slot]          │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │                         │
    │  CodeMirror editor      │
    │  + preview blocks       │
    │                         │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component MarkdownCard
  desc: Read-only preview card for embedding a Document in other surfaces.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text
```

```mdl
component EditableMarkdownCard
  desc: Inline-editable card variant used when data.editable is true.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text
```

## Operations

```mdl
op create
  desc: Creates a new markdown Document and adds it to the active space.
  input:
    name: string
    content: string
  output: string                # DXN of created Document
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op open
  desc: Reads the current contents of a markdown Document.
  input:
    doc: Ref<Document>
  output: string                # current Document content
  effects: [echo:read]
```

```mdl
op update
  desc: Applies a set of find/replace edits to a markdown Document.
  input:
    doc: Ref<Document>
    edits: Edit[]               # { oldString, newString, replaceAll? }
  output: string                # new Document content
  errors:
    NotFound: oldString not present in document
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op scrollToAnchor
  desc: Scrolls the editor for the attendable surface to a cursor position.
  input:
    subject: string             # attendable ID
    cursor: string
    ref?: string                # e.g. comment thread ID
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Edit Document

  req F-1.1: Editor opens Document.content as a collaborative CodeMirror surface.
  req F-1.2: Edits replicate to all peers via ECHO Text.
  req F-1.3: Document.name renders as the surface title; fallbackName used when name is empty.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: View Modes

  req F-2.1: Document opens in settings.defaultViewMode (source | preview | readonly).
  req F-2.2:
    when: user toggles view mode
    then: editor switches between source and preview; state persists per Document

  req F-2.3:
    when: viewMode is readonly
    then: editor is non-editable; toolbar hidden
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Formatting Toolbar

  req F-3.1:
    when: settings.toolbar is true
    then: formatting toolbar shown above editor with bold, italic, headings, lists, links

  req F-3.2: Toolbar surfaces toolbar-disposition actions from the app graph for the current attendable.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Inline References

  req F-4.1:
    when: user types `@` in the editor
    then: link query opens with objects from the active space

  req F-4.2:
    when: user selects a reference
    then: a link to the object DXN is inserted at the cursor

  req F-4.3:
    when: user clicks a reference
    then: LayoutOperation.Open invoked for the linked object
```

```mdl
feat F-5: File Upload

  req F-5.1:
    when: user drops an image onto the editor
    then: file uploaded via AppCapabilities.FileUploader and inserted as a markdown image
```

```mdl
feat F-6: AI Editing

  req F-6.1: Plugin contributes a Skill exposing op:create, op:open, op:update as tools.
  req F-6.2:
    when: agent invokes op:update
    then: edits applied as ordered oldString → newString diffs against Document.content
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Comments

  req F-7.1: Editor supports anchored comment threads on text ranges.
  req F-7.2:
    when: settings.commentAgentMode is `auto`
    then: every new user message in a thread triggers the comment agent

  req F-7.3:
    when: settings.commentAgentMode is `mention`
    then: agent responds only when the message contains its @name
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create document
  given: user has an open space
  when: op:create invoked with { name: "Notes", content: "# Hello" }
  then:
    - new Document persisted to ECHO
    - Document.name === "Notes"
    - Document.content target contains "# Hello"
```

```mdl
test T-2: Apply edit
  given: Document.content is "There is a tyop."
  when: op:update invoked with edits [{ oldString: "tyop", newString: "typo" }]
  then:
    - Document.content becomes "There is a typo."
```

```mdl
test T-3: Toggle view mode
  given: Document open, settings.defaultViewMode === source
  when: user toggles view mode
  then:
    - editor renders preview
    - reload restores preview mode for this Document
```

```mdl
test T-4: Reference autocomplete
  given: Document open, space contains object "ProjectX"
  when: user types `@Proj`
  then:
    - link query shows ProjectX
    - selecting it inserts a DXN link at the cursor
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```
